The paper discusses the use of deep learning for visual analysis, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The focus on compressing and transmitting intermediate-layer deep learning features suggests a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the balance between computational load, transmission load, and generalization ability, which suggests a potential overlap with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
